Wait time was 1 hour and 10 minutes!  I'm a door dasher and the customer had ordered their food on Christmas. I get there and I see 6 DoorDashers and 3 GrubHubers waiting in addition to 1 customer who had ordered over the phone. About 10 minutes later 2 additional customers who had called in came in because they were told it would be a 10 minute wait so they were lied to. Cheng's Garden had lost two of the ticker orders of the non-delivery people that were waiting and they were NOT happy. Personally, I wasn't happy because as a DoorDasher we make a low commission and we are lucky if the customer even tips $2.00. So it wasn't worth it for that long wait time and low tip. I asked the cashier where my customer's order was but she blew me off. I personally will not order from here ever and I will start rejecting DoorDash orders from here.
Food is decent however be prepared for the longest wait time for delivery. I’m .19 miles away and it still takes at least and hour usually closer to 2 regardless of what’s ordered.

Our first clue should have been that we were the only customers in the place at noon on a Wednesday. The lady at the counter was rude but I can handle rude as long as the food is tasty. The food SUCKED. We had actually come to eat at the wonderful Cafe Fusion next door but it was closed. So we decided to try this place. What a waste of time and money. The food was inedible. I ordered orange chicken and my husband ordered sesame chicken. Both were in the exact same horrible tasting sauce. The only difference was his chicken had sesame seeds, uncooked, sprinkled on it. While we were pushing our food around on our styrofoam plates with our plastic forks looking for one mosel of redeemable food, i kept smelling cigarettes but couldnt figure out from where.  When I went to throw our food away, i found the source of the stench. The trashcan reeked of cigarette butts. As we pulled away, vowing to ourselves never to return,  the counter lady came outside to smoke, glaring at us the whole time. Lol. She must have plenty of time to smoke since there weren't any other customers or calls while we were there. Now we know why!!

We had a long wait about 20 minutes. They forgot our egg rolls and the food was bad. My Kung pao chicken had a burnt flavor and my sisters mingolion chicken was dry and way over cooked. Worst Chinese I’ve had in DesMoines and I eat it a lot!

Fourty dollars down the drain for the worst food I have had in a while. First time customer and last time as well, after reading other customers experiences as well as tasting the dish they brought me today.  I ordered the four season's dish, and the pork was leathery and over cooked, the beef was super soft like disgusting pure fat, veggies under cooked and sauce was bland. I wish I had read reviews before buying this over priced nastiness.  My experience was a 2 star at best, but after reading how they've treated others they've lost a star as well. Bottom line: don't eat here. There are better Asian restaurants around town. Much, much better.

Good rice chicken and egg roll. I Come here a lot.

My review is for the Merle Hay Road location. Not the 14th Street one.  AVOID! DOUBLE CHARGED A $50 order after promising they wouldn't. Used their online ordering system to place a pick up order. My husband went to pick it up and paid, then had to wait. On his way out the door he was stopped and was told that he would have to pay... again. The lady told him that the first time he ran the card was not actually the payment. It was just acknowledging the order and that he wasn't actually charged. Confused, but assuming she knows what she's talking about, he swiped his card again. But lo and behold, she lied! There are now TWO charges on my bank statement. The online ordering company says one will be reversed and were totally rude as well. But even if one of the charges is reversed, our funds are unavailable for use for three or four days. $100 for $50 order that was probably only worth $30 really sucks. Some of the food was alright. The orange chicken was good as were the egg rolls. The lo mein was super greasy and flavorless.  Either they are too stupid to run their OWN online ordering system or they are scam artists. Either way, avoid this place. It's not worth the hassle at all. We order take out maybe once a year. Thanks for ruining the experience and causing our paycheck to paycheck family so much undue burden. We plan for these types of expenditures. How do I put food in the fridge and gas in the car while you toy with us over the $50 you stole?? Bad business.

We still paid extra and some of us including my little ones got sick with stomach ache that lasted for 2 days. Because not to get her mad because you dont know if they put something else or get charged more that what is supposed to. Also there is a box of popsicle candy and it is written .50cents each or 3 for $1.00 dollar. But she charged me $1.00 dollar each popsicle and when back to get the rest of the money and she got mad and didnt want to give me back the rest until i showed her the box that says 3 for $1.00.  I told her not to get mad and later she went to the table and told us " the next time you come back make sure you know what you going to order so you dont make me waste time telling the cooks what you want". noodles were overcooked and tasted like boxed food. Service was horrible, and delivery takes 90 minutes. Cheng's isn't worth your time or money.
Probably the best Chinese take out in the Des Moines area.
so i love the fact they deliver lat time i ordered food it did take a while for me to get it but once i got my food it was well done and amazing

The service was wonderful. I called I an order for pick up and it was ready in about 15 minutes. We ordered 3 meals, and three sides so I was impressed. However the food was VERY bland. I ordered garlic beef- it was supposed to be spicy, not so much. The beef and broccoli wasn't any better. The cashew chicken was less than desirable. Crab Rangoon was decent, as were the egg rolls. Over all not the best place for Chinese, I probably won't be going there again.

I always go to this location when I'm hungry. I always seem to get the young guy working the counter, and he's always super helpful. Every time I go in, I ask him what he recommends, and every time the food is great. I haven't had an issue with inconsistent food, or bad service. My only (small) complaint is that since I live outside the delivery area, I go in to get carry out. If I don't order ahead, then I'm stuck waiting for upwards of 10 minutes. It's not too big of an issue for me, but it might be for someone else. Overall, a great experience every time.

Food is usually not bad.  Unfortunately inconsistent.  My sweet and sour shrimp was horribly over cooked, two pieces had the shrimp inside the batter crunchy and hard.  My co-worker ordered white rice with her meal and received pork fried rice - she can't eat pork!  I faxed them and asked for the two meals to be comped the next week and to contact me and then NEVER RESPONDED.  In addition, I have tangled with the lady that sometimes answers the phone.  She is not polite, she argued with me about MY order. Others in my office have complained about her as well.  It's unfortunate since their prices are good, the food is usually good, but don't provide good customer service so I won't be ordering from them any longer.

I wanted to order food to go, however, when I called in the owner at the time (John) told me that I needed to place an order because he was busy. As I asked questions about the menu he was short and didn't want to explain anything to me. When i questioned further about the business model and how as and owner he would turn away business because I didn't know what all he served he then informed me that he was a manager. NEVER buy from here, no matter how the food is. As a firm believer in the American dream I will say that business should be built on hard work, integrity, and a great product. None of that was show tonight here.

I got the Mongolian beef and the wife got the honey chicken both come with pork fried rice and two crab ragoons from the lunch menu. The rice was perfectly cooked. Beef had a great flavor and ragoons wee good too. We haven't had any better Chinese food anywhere that comes close to this place and that's including Sam's fine dining.

Every time I call they are extremely polite. My order always shows up earlier than expected and piping hot! Also you can tell the crab rangoon is not frozen; thank goodness! They have my business over panda express or hy-vee any day!!!!!

The food is literally inedible and is way overpriced, especially considering half of it is nasty rice (half of which is onions- like half a freakin onion). Oh yea, the rice isn't on the side- it's half of your meal. The egg rolls are nearly as bad. To top it off, talking on the phone to them is far more of a challenge than I have ever encountered at any other Chinese restaurant.

Having lived in SF for many years. I find the food mediocre  at best and very overpriced for the area. Just tried the egg rolls.. very unhappy  they had no flavor no texture  just a bunch of mush.. . But being this is Des Moines Iowa. and one of the few Asian restaurants that deliver.. What can I expect. .
This place is overpriced for what you get. Don't dine-in unless you want bad service.
The potstickers were the best I have had in a long time. I got the general tso's chicken it was pretty good. The rice was nothing special.
Ugh...I make better chinese food. The flavors were not good and the appearance of the food was even worse. Save your money.

I love the people there, they are very friendly and always have a smile on their face. I love how the food is cooked on the spot to the costumers wants or needs. Turn around time from order to in hand is great!

Food used to be amazing and now it is horrible!!!! They changed ingredients and it's a cheap food. Horrible I won't be back.
